30 recovery mechanisms, as proposed by the office of energy resources or the division of public
31 utilities and carriers, that allocate the costs of new, electric-transmission and natural-gas-pipeline
32 infrastructure and capacity projects selected pursuant to the provisions of this chapter to ratepayers,
33 such that costs are shared among participating states in an equitable manner; and
34 (4) To the extent that the public utility company that provides electric distribution as
